  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pork-apple-and-mustard-casserole/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a <strong>high heat</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced pork shoulder </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pork-apple-and-mustard-casserole/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and roughly chop your <strong>carrots</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> into large rounds and wash thoroughly to remove any grit</p><p>Dice your <strong>apple[s]</strong> (skin on) and discard the core[s]</p><p>Cut your<strong> potato[es]</strong> into large bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pork-apple-and-mustard-casserole/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has started to brown, add the <strong>chopped carrots</strong>, <strong>leek</strong>, <strong>apple </strong>and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potato </strong>with your <strong>dried sage </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pork-apple-and-mustard-casserole/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and mix it all together and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[580ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[770ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and stir it all together</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and put in the oven, covered, for an initial 55 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pork-apple-and-mustard-casserole/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pork-apple-and-mustard-casserole/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 55 min, stir through your <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and most<strong> </strong>of your <strong>double cream </strong>(save a drizzle for a garnish!)<strong> </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven, uncovered, for a final 5 min or until the potatoes are tender and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>creamy pork, apple & mustard casserole</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pork-apple-and-mustard-casserole/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drizzle the <strong>creamy pork, apple & mustard casserole </strong>with the <strong>remaining double cream</strong></p><p>Finish with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
